snippet.textDisplay: Hey, just a tip. I saw some of the gritty looking paint from your paint job, the reason this tends to happen, especially to your Jeep this time is because the ambient air temperature and Jeep were very warm from the 3 heaters that the paint partially dried mid spray before it was attached to the panels. This creates that gritty feeling and appearance. On the bright side you guys do so well buffing that it comes out looking real nice. Keep up the amazing work!
